**a.)** For this problem, we will solve for the effective annual interest using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Effective Annual Interest}&=\dfrac{(1+\text{Rate on borrowed funds})^\text{Number of compounding periods}-1}{(1-\text{Rate on compensating balance}}
\end{aligned}$$

Since the rate is given quarterly, then that means that we have $4$ compounding periods in a year. To solve for the effective annual interest of this, we can simply substitute the values:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Effective Annual Interest}&=\dfrac{(1+0.0185)^4-1}{1-0.045}\\[15 pt]
&=0.0797
\end{aligned}$$

The Effective Annual Interest of this is $0.0797$ or $7.97\%$
